---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service for Amply music gear rentals — rental conditions, payment, damage policy, and cancellations."
>
  <div class="page-container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1 class="display-lg">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>1. Rental Agreement</h2>
      <p>By placing a rental order with Amply, you agree to these Terms of Service. A rental agreement is formed when Amply confirms your booking in writing (via email or WhatsApp). Amply reserves the right to decline any rental request.</p>

      <h2>2. Payment</h2>
      <p>Full rental payment is due before delivery. After order confirmation, we will share UPI or bank transfer details. Delivery will not proceed until payment is received. Prices displayed on the website are in Indian Rupees (INR) and are inclusive of delivery and setup within Ahmedabad city limits.</p>

      <h2>3. Delivery & Setup</h2>
      <p>Amply will deliver and set up all rented equipment at your specified venue at the agreed time. A representative from your event must be present to receive the equipment. Setup times will be agreed upon at the time of booking.</p>

      <h2>4. Collection</h2>
      <p>Equipment will be collected by Amply at the end of the rental period at the agreed time. You are responsible for ensuring all equipment is available and accessible for collection. Late returns may incur additional charges at the standard daily rate.</p>

      <h2>5. Care of Equipment</h2>
      <p>You are responsible for the rented equipment from the time of delivery until collection. Equipment must be used only for its intended purpose and handled with reasonable care. Do not attempt to repair, modify, or move equipment to a different location without prior written consent from Amply.</p>

      <h2>6. Damage & Loss</h2>
      <p>Any damage to or loss of rented equipment beyond normal wear and tear is your responsibility. Amply will assess damage after collection and invoice you for repair or replacement costs at current market rates. Deliberate damage or theft will be reported to the appropriate authorities.</p>

      <h2>7. Cancellations & Refunds</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Cancellations made more than 48 hours before the delivery time: full refund.</li>
        <li>Cancellations made 24–48 hours before delivery: 50% refund.</li>
        <li>Cancellations made less than 24 hours before delivery: no refund.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Amply reserves the right to cancel a booking due to unforeseen circumstances (equipment failure, force majeure). In such cases, a full refund will be provided.</p>

      <h2>8. Liability</h2>
      <p>Amply's liability is limited to the value of the rental fee paid. We are not liable for any indirect, consequential, or special damages arising from the use or unavailability of rented equipment. You are responsible for ensuring the venue is suitable and safe for the equipment.</p>

      <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of India. Any disputes shall be subject to the jurisdiction of the courts of Ahmedabad, Gujarat.</p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about these Terms, contact us at:<br />
      <strong>Amply</strong><br />
      Ahmedabad, Gujarat, India<br />
      <a href="mailto:hello@amply.in">hello@amply.in</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-container { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 64px 24px 96px; }
  .page-header { margin-bottom: 48px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-hairline); padding-bottom: 32px; }
  .page-header h1 { margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .last-updated { font-size: 13px; color: var(--color-mute); margin: 0; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .page-container { padding: 40px 20px 72px; } }
</style>
